Luanda &mdash; Angola's ambassadors to the Democratic Republic of Congo, Emilio Jos&eacute; de Carvalho Guerra, and to the Republic of Serbia, Jos&eacute; Jo&atilde;o Manuel, were fired on Thursday by the Angolan President, Jos&eacute; Eduardo dos Santos.The dismissals were confirmed in a press release from the President's Civil Office, which reached Angop on Thursday.The President of the Republic appointed Augusto da Silva Cunha as the Angolan ambassador to Ghana, Em&iacute;lio Jos&eacute; de Carvalho Guerra, to the position of ambassador to Serbia and Jos&eacute; Jo&atilde;o Manuel, as the ambassador to DR Congo.